{"lemma":"رُقِيِّ","slug":"رُقِيِّ","root":"ر.ق.#","root_slug":"ر-ق-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ق-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رُقِيّ","root":"رقي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16281","n16413"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rise, to ascend","examples":[{"text":"أَوْ يَكُونَ لَكَ بَيْتٌ مِنْ زُخْرُفٍ أَوْ تَرْقَىٰ فِي السَّمَاءِ","english":"or until you have a house of gold, or you ascend into heaven."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be promoted"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقِيَ (raqiya) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَى (raqā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقِيَ (raqiya) (form I): ascension","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَنْ نُؤْمِنَ لِرُقِيِّكَ حَتَّىٰ تُنَزِّلَ عَلَيْنَا كِتَابًا نَقْرَؤُهُ","english":"and even then we will not believe in your ascension until you bring down to us a book that we can read."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَى (raqā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16281","headword_ar":"رُقَّى","root":"rq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araq~u","text_ar":"اَرَقُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16413","headword_ar":"رَقِىَ","root":"rqY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroqaY","text_ar":"يَرْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqiY~N","text_ar":"رُقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA, [but this inf. n. is omitted in the CK,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqoYN","text_ar":"رَقْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [but this is omitted in my MS. copy of the K,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ascended,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtqY","text_ar":"ارتقى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trq~Y","text_ar":"ترقّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ascended a ladder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiytu fiyhi","text_ar":"رَقِيتُ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, in the Mgh"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiYa fyh","text_ar":"رَقِىَ فيه"},{"kind":"text","text":",) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqiY~N","text_ar":"رُقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqoYN","text_ar":"رَقْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artqyt","text_ar":"ارتقيت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, * Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trq~yt","text_ar":"ترقّيت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, * Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ascended it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) namely, a ladder, or a stair, (S, Mgh, Msb,) &c.: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiytu Aljabala","text_ar":"رَقِيتُ الجَبَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aToHa","text_ar":"السَّطْحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) the verb being thus trans. by itself, (Msb, TA,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) and likewise with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ascended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted, upon the mountain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the house-top:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtqY","text_ar":"ارتقى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in like manner trans. without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqadi","text_ar":"لَقَدِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEobFA","text_ar":"صَعْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@rotaqayota murotaqFY","text_ar":"ا@رْتَقَيْتَ مُرْتَقًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast indeed ascended a difficult place of ascent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airoqa EalaY ZaloEika","text_ar":"اِرْقَ عَلَى ظَلْعِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ascend thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to thy limping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as far as thou art able to do so, and impose not upon thyself that which thou art not able to perform."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA. [Some, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airoqa","text_ar":"اِرْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiroqaA^o","text_ar":"اِرْقَاْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airoqi","text_ar":"اِرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from the verb mentioned in the next sentence; and some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqA^","text_ar":"رقا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZlE","text_ar":"ظلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaAhu","text_ar":"رَقَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroqiY","text_ar":"يَرْقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqoyapN","text_ar":"رُقْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqoY","text_ar":"رَقْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Mgh, Msb, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqiY~N","text_ar":"رُقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He charmed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaw~a*ahu","text_ar":"عَوَّذَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invoking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he puffed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sputtered, upon his charm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafava","text_ar":"نَفَثَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Euw*atihi","text_ar":"فِى عُوذَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, K:) [it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he charmed him"},{"kind":"text","text":"from, or against, such a thing; ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino ka*aA","text_ar":"مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he enchanted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascinated him; by uttering a spell;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by tying knots in a thread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"string, and puffing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sputtering, upon them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by both these actions combined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the last chap. but one of the Kur-án:] the epithet applied to the performer is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAqK","text_ar":"رَاقٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Charming;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (S, Mgh, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raq~aA='N","text_ar":"رَقَّا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A charmer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who habitually practises charming;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (JK, K, TA:) and the epithet applied to the person who is the object of the performance is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroqiY~N","text_ar":"مَرْقِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Charmed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (JK, TA.) In the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airoqi EalaY raA^osiY mina AlS~udaAEi","text_ar":"اِرْقِ عَلَى رَاْسِى مِنَ الصُّدَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Charm thou me"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaw~i*oniY","text_ar":"عَوِّذْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charm thou my head against the headache"},{"kind":"text","text":"]), the verb is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is as though it implied the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiqor~A^o","text_ar":"اِقْرّاْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. “ recite thou ” a spell] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aunofuvo","text_ar":"اُنْفُثْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. “ puff, ” or “ sputter, ” upon knots]. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","JK","S","Mgh","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}